Package org.apache.commons.pool2.impl

Class EvictionConfig

java.lang.Object
org.apache.commons.pool2.impl.EvictionConfig
public class EvictionConfig extends Object
This class is used by pool implementations to pass configuration information to EvictionPolicy instances. The EvictionPolicy may also have its own specific configuration attributes.

This class is immutable and thread-safe.

Since:
2.0

  • Constructor Details

    • EvictionConfig

      public EvictionConfig(Duration idleEvictDuration, Duration idleSoftEvictDuration, int minIdle)
      Creates a new eviction configuration with the specified parameters. Instances are immutable.
      Parameters:
      idleEvictDuration - Expected to be provided by BaseGenericObjectPool.getMinEvictableIdleDuration()
      idleSoftEvictDuration - Expected to be provided by BaseGenericObjectPool.getSoftMinEvictableIdleDuration()
      minIdle - Expected to be provided by GenericObjectPool.getMinIdle() or GenericKeyedObjectPool.getMinIdlePerKey()
      Since:
      2.10.0
